The paper discusses the effectiveness of small neural ensembles in solving high-dimensional problems, which is a topic closely related to neural networks and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical physics and concentration of measure theory, which are relevant to topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the organization of complex memories in ensembles of single neurons, which is relevant to topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
